To satisfy the tie-breaking rule (“round down to 365.00 when the difference to the nearest 5 is in the middle exactly”), I should avoid `MROUND`, since midpoint behavior may round up. A safer formula is:

`=INT(B1/5)*5+IF(MOD(B1,5)>2.5,5,0)`

This rounds to the nearest 5, but when the remainder is exactly `2.5`, it stays on the lower multiple of 5. For `367.5`, that yields `365`.

